HEADWORD: Contracture
<hw>Con*trac"ture</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>contractura</ets> a drawing together.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A state of permanent rigidity or contraction of the muscles,
generally of the flexor muscles.</def>⟦br⟧
